The White House is hosting the first-ever White House Summit on Working Families to discuss and find solutions for the economic stresses and emotional strains that families face. In order for American businesses and the country as a whole to remain competitive and successful, workplace policies need to be updated for the 21st century. The Council of Economic Advisers released a report called "Nine Facts About American Families and Work" which highlights the changes needed to ensure long-term economic growth, maintain competitiveness, improve the well-being of Americans, and utilize America's talent. The report can be accessed via the provided link.